<p><strong>Position:</strong> Director of Transportation Policy, Reason Foundation</p>

<p><strong>Background:</strong><br />
Robert Poole is the Director of Transportation Policy at the Reason Foundation, where he has worked extensively on transportation policy, infrastructure financing, and privatization of public services. He is a recognized expert in public policy analysis, with a particular focus on advocating for market-based solutions to public sector challenges. Poole has advised several U.S. administrations on transportation and infrastructure issues, including roles in advisory capacities during the Reagan, Bush, and Clinton administrations.</p>

